                        <p class="inner-paragraph font-size-medium blue-color"><b>What is the CFA Exam? And What Is It For?</b></p>
                        <p class="inner-paragraph">The CFA exam certifies individuals as Certified Financial Analysts (CFA) and allows them to become part of the extensive CFA Charter, which is globally recognized. 190+ finance societies are affiliated with it globally, adding to the privilege's impact. The exam qualifies individuals for emerging roles in investment and portfolio management, risk assessment, venture capital, corporate finance, academia, and research. Our <b><a href="https://www.classhelpusa.com/online-exam-help">online exam helpers</a></b> guides and answers all your queries related to the impact of the certification and the exam course outline.</p>
                        <p class="inner-paragraph font-size-medium blue-color"><b>Exam Pattern And Duration for CFA Charter</b></p>
                        <p class="inner-paragraph">The CFA Certification Program has three levels</p>
                        <p class="inner-paragraph font-size-medium black-color"><b>CFA Level I</b></p>
                        <p class="inner-paragraph">It consists of 180 multiple-choice questions. The total duration of this exam is 4 hours and 30 minutes, which is split into two equal sessions of 2 hours and 15 minutes each. Each session requires 90 questions to be attempted. There is an optional break between these two sessions. The Level I exam assesses basic knowledge of essential terms and formulas related to the investment industry.</p>
                        <p class="inner-paragraph font-size-medium black-color"><b>CFA Level II</b></p>
                        <p class="inner-paragraph">It consists of 11 short case studies or case statements with 88 multiple-choice questions that need to be answered as per the provided case studies along with them. The duration of the exam is 4 hours and 24 minutes, divided into two sessions of 2 hours and 12 minutes with an optional break between them. Each session consists of an exam of 11 question sets, comprising a total of 22 sets of cases, out of which 20 are graded and 2 are not. The Level II exam checks your ability to analyse different scenarios and apply your knowledge to the best solution.</p>
                        <p class="inner-paragraph font-size-medium black-color"><b>CFA Level III</b></p>
                        <p class="inner-paragraph">It consists of 11 question sets, which can be a variable mix of question item sets or essay sets, with either 6 item sets and 5 essay sets or 5 item sets and 6 essay sets, each with their own constructed response questions (CRQs) to be answered after careful analysis of essay or item sets both including vignettes. Vignettes are mini business case studies that are for analysis, and then, based on extracted and understood information, constructed responses are provided in the exams. </p>
                        <p class="inner-paragraph">Like Level II, 20 sets are graded, while one item set and one essay set are on a trial basis and not graded. Level III evaluates the real-world application of financial knowledge to real-life scenarios via careful understanding of complex reality-based problems.</p>
                        <p class="inner-paragraph font-size-medium blue-color"><b>When Can The CFA Exam be taken?</b></p>
                        <p class="inner-paragraph">Undergraduates can take the attempt within 23 months of graduation in the offered exam cycles, for which information is available on the CFA course sites. For working professionals who have already graduated, they can take the exam whenever they like in the designated cycles. 4000+ hours of work and educational hours are necessary before a candidate appears in this exam. With the exam of the CFA course Levels, PSMs (Practical Skills Module) are also required to be completed via the provided course materials and tasks. These modules are different for each level and must be completed before the announcement of the results of each Level attempt. These modules typically range from 10 to 15 hours.</p>
                        
